<link href="adcp.css" rel="stylesheet"><entry><xh5> bring someone under control • bring someone under one’s control</xh5><p> <i>bring someone under control—</i>subject a person to restraint of behavior: Princess Máxima tried to <u>bring the children under control</u> with a stern face, but failed at the attempt.</p><p> <i>bring someone under one’s control—</i>achieve dominion over a person; subject smb. to one’s authority: The dictator was at last able to <u>bring the army under his control</u>.</p> </entry>
